Award Nomination Submission – DATA Champion Award

1. Team Name:
Credit Risk Reporting and Transformation (CRRT)

2. Team Members:
	•	

3. Line of Business:
Corporate Risk

⸻

4. Initiative / Contribution Description

The BRM (Business Rules Management) Tool is a no-code/low-code solution designed to empower business users to manage data transformation, movement, and quality checks in a fully automated and intuitive manner. It leverages a rules-based engine that enables business users—without heavy reliance on IT—to create, modify, and execute data rules.

Key differentiator: BRM automatically captures metadata and data lineage whenever a rule is created, updated, or deleted, ensuring end-to-end traceability and governance without manual intervention.

⸻

5. Business Challenge & Significance

Prior to BRM, data transformation and quality checks were highly manual, IT-dependent, and error-prone. This led to longer delivery timelines, fragmented controls, and limited transparency into lineage. The significant challenge addressed was:
	•	Eliminating dependency on technical coding resources for rule development.
	•	Improving speed and accuracy in delivering reporting and transformation solutions.
	•	Providing audit-ready lineage and governance with zero additional overhead.

By solving these, BRM directly supported regulatory compliance, data integrity, and faster time-to-market for risk reporting.

⸻

6. Measurable Outcomes & Business Impact
	•	Efficiency Gains: 60–70% reduction in turnaround time for building and deploying data rules.
	•	Cost Savings: Lowered IT development effort by shifting ownership of rule creation to business SMEs.
	•	Risk Reduction: Automated lineage capture reduces operational risk by ensuring compliance with internal and regulatory audit requirements.
	•	Scalability: Enabled transformation of large volumes of risk data across multiple platforms consistently.
	•	Adoption: Business teams can now simulate, test, and deploy rules independently, creating a culture of self-service analytics and automation.

⸻

7. Innovative Methodologies & Technologies
	•	No-code/low-code design: Business-driven automation for data transformation.
	•	Automated metadata & lineage capture: Eliminates manual documentation and enforces governance by design.
	•	Integrated validations: In-built quality checks ensure data accuracy before consumption.
	•	Advanced UI (PyQt5-based): Intuitive visual management of rules, scheduling, simulations, and lineage graphs.
	•	Predictive & AI extensions: Foundations laid for anomaly detection and advanced analytics on execution patterns.

⸻

8. Cross-Functional Collaboration & Alignment
	•	The tool was co-designed with business stakeholders, IT, and data governance teams, ensuring alignment with enterprise standards.
	•	Enabled seamless collaboration across Corporate Risk, Technology, and Compliance, reducing silos and fostering a “business-owned, IT-enabled” model.
	•	Provided governance teams with automated transparency, while giving business users flexibility and agility.

⸻

9. Differentiation & Problem-Solving Approach
	•	Tackled the longstanding gap between business agility vs. IT dependency by reimagining data transformation as a business-owned process.
	•	Designed a future-proof, modular system capable of scaling across multiple LOBs.
	•	Balanced innovation (automation + lineage capture) with compliance and governance requirements.

⸻

10. Advancements in Data & AI Capabilities
	•	Data Quality: Built-in validations improved data integrity and reduced errors in downstream reporting.
	•	Analytics Enablement: Faster, trusted data flows enhanced risk analysis and decision-making.
	•	AI Readiness: Introduced predictive analytics modules (e.g., anomaly detection in rule execution) to support AI-driven governance.
	•	Technology Adoption: Pioneered a self-service automation model, accelerating digital transformation across risk reporting.

⸻

11. Data Governance & Responsible Practices
	•	Automated lineage capture ensures accuracy, consistency, and traceability across all data flows.
	•	Audit logs and approval workflows ensure security, accountability, and compliance.
	•	Locks, validations, and controlled scheduling ensure rules cannot be altered without proper governance.

⸻

12. Alignment to Enterprise Strategy

This initiative directly supports the organization’s Data, Analytics, and AI strategy by:
	•	Enabling trusted data pipelines with integrity and governance.
	•	Accelerating digital transformation through low-code/no-code adoption.
	•	Empowering business users to take ownership of transformation while reducing dependency on IT resources.
	•	Laying a foundation for AI-driven governance and automation in risk reporting.

⸻

13. Why CRRT is a Strong Candidate for the DATA Champion Award

The CRRT team’s BRM tool exemplifies innovation, governance, and empowerment:
	•	It democratizes data transformation by placing control in business users’ hands.
	•	It inspires other teams by showing how automation and governance can coexist seamlessly.
	•	It sets a new standard of efficiency, transparency, and compliance within the Corporate Risk function.
	•	The initiative is a scalable enterprise solution that can extend beyond Corporate Risk, making it a blueprint for the future of data-driven decision-making.

⸻

⭐ Inspiration Factor: By bridging the gap between business needs and technology controls, the CRRT team has demonstrated how innovation with responsibility can redefine the way data is managed, governed, and used for decision-making.

